## Forms

**`forms.css`** is visual-only: field layout, control appearance, states, messages.

**Superforms** is the standard form behavior library and is already installed in this template.

- Use Superforms server actions for all forms with submission behavior.
- Do not build custom form submission handlers.
- Do not add validation logic to CSS or components.
- Put form schemas in `src/lib/forms/` (for example, `src/lib/forms/contact.schema.ts`).
- Reuse the live contact form at `src/routes/contact/` as the reference pattern for validation, DB persistence, email notification, transactional outbox events, honeypot handling, and rate limiting.
- For lead-capture or workflow-starting forms, follow `docs/forms/README.md`: add a typed source table, register the form in `src/lib/server/forms/registry.ts`, add outbox handlers in `src/lib/server/automation/registry.ts`, and run `bun run forms:check`.
- For a new typed starter, run `bun run scaffold:form -- --slug=<form-id>`, review the generated fields, then run `bun run db:generate`. Use `bun run forms:ops` for redacted operator inspection.

## Content and CMS

Full docs: [docs/cms/README.md](docs/cms/README.md) · Contract: [docs/cms/sveltia-content-contract.md](docs/cms/sveltia-content-contract.md)

- **CMS editor:** `/admin` — Sveltia CMS (configure `backend.repo` in `static/admin/config.yml`)
- **Content directory:** `content/` — Git-backed YAML and Markdown files
- **Loaders:** `src/lib/content/` — `loadHomePage()`, `loadArticle()`, `loadArticles()`, etc.
- **Schemas:** `src/lib/content/schemas.ts` — shared Valibot content contract
- **Types:** `src/lib/content/types.ts` — derived from the schemas
- **CMS config:** `static/admin/config.yml` — editor UI fields, cross-checked against schemas

### Parser rules — critical, do not mix

| File type                                                                 | Parser          | Notes                                 |
| ------------------------------------------------------------------------- | --------------- | ------------------------------------- |
| `content/pages/*.yml`, `content/team/*.yml`, `content/testimonials/*.yml` | **js-yaml**     | Pure YAML, no `---` delimiters        |
| `content/articles/*.md`                                                   | **gray-matter** | Remap `.content` → `.body` explicitly |

- Never use gray-matter for pure YAML files
- Never use js-yaml for Markdown frontmatter files
- Always remap gray-matter body: `return { ...data, body: content }` — never `data.body`
- Validate parsed content with `src/lib/content/schemas.ts`; do not cast parsed CMS data directly
- File-reading routes must use `+page.server.ts`, not `+page.ts`

### Sveltia CMS gotchas

- Field names in `config.yml` = `src/lib/content/schemas.ts` keys = TypeScript properties = Svelte component data keys — they are a contract
- Never rename a field without updating config, content files, types, loaders, components, and docs
- Use `snake_case` for all YAML field names
- Do not use `content` or `data` as field names — they clash with loader conventions
- CMS image fields must render through `CmsImage`, not bare `<img>`
- Local CMS editing uses Sveltia's **Work with Local Repository** browser flow; do not add `local_backend` to `config.yml`
- To add a collection: schema + config + starter file + loader + route/SEO + docs
- `static/admin/index.html` must use a plain `<script src="/admin/sveltia/sveltia-cms.js">` in `<body>` — no stylesheet link, no `type="module"`. The bundle is vendored from `node_modules/@sveltia/cms` by `scripts/vendor-sveltia.ts` (postinstall hook); `static/admin/sveltia/` is gitignored. Sveltia bundles its styles in the JS file and is not an ES module. Do not copy Static CMS / Netlify CMS patterns here, and do not switch back to loading from `https://unpkg.com` — the `/admin` CSP intentionally drops that origin and `'unsafe-eval'`.

### AI reference for config.yml edits

When editing `static/admin/config.yml`, use Sveltia's official AI-readable docs rather than Netlify CMS or Static CMS examples:

- `https://sveltiacms.app/llms.txt` — quick reference (use by default)
- `https://sveltiacms.app/llms-full.txt` — full reference (large; fetch only for complex config work)

Do not commit either file to this repo. They are labeled work-in-progress; when in doubt, trust the working config over the reference. See [docs/cms/sveltia-ai-reference.md](docs/cms/sveltia-ai-reference.md) for the full policy.

The site's own `/llms.txt` route (`src/routes/llms.txt/+server.ts`) is unrelated — it is a public AI/SEO disclosure for crawlers indexing the generated website, not CMS documentation.

## Observability and error handling

Full docs: [docs/observability/README.md](docs/observability/README.md)

This project uses the template's baseline observability spine. [Note any optional extensions activated for this project — Sentry, n8n error workflow, OpenTelemetry, external uptime monitor — or state explicitly that none are enabled.]

- Structured server logging: `src/lib/server/logger.ts` — use instead of `console.error`
- Request IDs: `src/hooks.server.ts` attaches `event.locals.requestId` to every request
- Safe errors: `src/lib/server/safe-error.ts` — separate public message from diagnostic detail
- Health endpoints: `/healthz` (process liveness, always 200) and `/readyz` (Postgres connectivity probe, 200/503)
- Error page: `src/routes/+error.svelte` — friendly, no stack traces
- Graceful shutdown: `serve.js` wrapper handles SIGTERM/SIGINT; tune drain window with `SHUTDOWN_TIMEOUT_MS` (default 10000ms)

**Agent rules:**

- Do not log secrets, tokens, cookies, or raw form payloads.
- Use `logger.error()` instead of `console.error()` for server-side errors.
- Use `toSafeError()` before returning error details to the browser.
- Do not add Sentry, OpenTelemetry, Grafana, or other observability services without explicit approval.
- Do not bypass `serve.js` by changing `CMD` back to `bun build/index.js` — the wrapper exists so Quadlet rolling restarts don't truncate in-flight responses.

## Automation (n8n)

Full docs: [docs/automations/README.md](docs/automations/README.md)

n8n is an optional external automation layer. The site works without it.

- **Do not** add n8n to `package.json`
- **Do not** import n8n packages in any SvelteKit module
- **Content automations:** n8n writes to `content/` via GitHub API — must follow `config.yml` schema
- **Runtime automations:** server action → Postgres source row + minimized outbox row → `bun run automation:worker` → signed provider delivery; exhausted failures land in `automation_dead_letters`
- User-facing actions must not call webhook providers directly
- HTTP providers with no URL skip cleanly when the worker runs
- Provider delivery failures must not break user-facing form submissions
- Production HTTP delivery must be HMAC-signed with the selected provider secret
- Do not commit real webhook URLs or secrets — use `.env.example` for variable names only
- AI-generated content must default to `draft: true` / `published: false`

## Secrets and environment

This project uses **SOPS + age** for secrets management (template default — see [docs/deployment/secrets.md](docs/deployment/secrets.md)).

- `secrets.yaml` — encrypted source of truth; commit only after `sops --encrypt --in-place secrets.yaml`
- `.env.example` — public contract for required variable names (no values)
- `.env` — rendered local/runtime artifact; gitignored; never the source of truth
- `~/.config/sops/age/keys.txt` — private age identity; never committed

Required env vars: see `.env.example`
Secrets workflow: `bun run secrets:render` / `bun run secrets:check`

### Secrets rules for agents

- Never commit `.env` or any `.env.*` file except `.env.example`.
- Never commit plaintext `secrets.yaml` (check for `sops:` block before staging).
- Never put real secret values in `src/lib/config/site.ts` or any module that can be imported by client-side code.
- Never import `DATABASE_URL`, `SESSION_SECRET`, or other private secrets into `+page.svelte` or client-accessible `src/lib/` files.
- Never add OpenBao, Doppler, Infisical, 1Password Secrets Automation, or cloud KMS integrations unless this project has explicitly changed this decision.
- When adding a new required environment variable, update `.env.example` and `secrets.example.yaml` together.

